Job Summary
Wise Soft Lab is seeking a motivated and enthusiastic Intern Software Engineer to join our dynamic software development team for Backend, Web and Mobile developments. This position offers an excellent opportunity to gain hands-on experience in real-world software development projects, contributing to the creation of innovative solutions

Minimum Qualification: Degree
Experience Level: Internship & Graduate
Experience Length: No Experience/Less than 1 year
Job Description/Requirements
Responsibilities:


Software Development: Assist in the design, development, and testing of software applications according to specifications. Contribute to coding tasks in programming languages such as Java, JavaScript, Kotlin, Swift, TypeScript or Dart under the guidance of senior engineers.
Quality Assurance: Participate in QA processes, including writing and executing test cases, identifying bugs, and working on fixes to improve the software quality.
Collaboration: Work closely with other engineering team members, participating in code reviews, design discussions, and project meetings to contribute to the development process and learn from experienced professionals.
Documentation: Help in creating and maintaining technical documentation for project planning, development processes, and user guides.
Learning and Development: Actively engage in learning opportunities provided by the company, including workshops, training sessions, and peer learning, to enhance your software engineering skills.

Qualifications:

A recent graduate of a Bachelor's or Master's program in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.
Foundational knowledge of programming languages such as JavaScript, TypeScript, Dart, Java and Kotlin.
Familiarity with software development methodologies (Agile, Scrum) is a plus.
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.
Strong communication skills, both verbal and written.
Eagerness to learn and adapt to new technologies and frameworks.

What can we offer you?

Mentorship from experienced software engineers and industry.
Hands-on experience with cutting-edge technologies and real-world software development projects.
A remote work culture with the opportunity to work at the office also.
Potential for future employment opportunities based on internship performance.
